# regulation-manager

## Functionality
Full CRUD management interface for QCVN environmental regulations. Allows users to create custom standards, edit parameters, import/export as JSON, and persist to the local filesystem via Tauri's FS plugin.

## Tasks
- List all available regulations (built-in + custom)
- Create new custom QCVN regulation with parameters (name, unit, limit, type)
- Edit existing regulation parameters
- Delete custom regulations
- Import regulations from JSON files
- Export regulations to JSON files
- Persist custom regulations to `AppData/regulations.json` via Tauri FS
- Reset to default built-in QCVN standards (QCVN 08-MT:2015, QCVN 14:2008, QCVN 05:2013)

## Purpose
Different environmental monitoring scenarios require different regulatory standards. This module gives users the **flexibility to define custom regulations** for specific water bodies, industrial discharge permits, or regional requirements beyond the 3 built-in QCVN standards.

## General Roadmap
- Currently `components/RegulationManager.tsx` (~31KB — the largest component) + `services/regulations.ts` (~4.7KB)
- Future: regulation templates for common scenarios
- Future: regulation versioning (track changes over time)
- Future: share regulations between team members

## Key Files
- `components/RegulationManager.tsx` — Full CRUD UI
- `services/regulations.ts` — Persistence and file I/O logic
- `constants.ts` — Built-in default QCVN standards
